64},{"id":"reczE75jW2yEqhF3M","ref":"Phil.2.3","text":"Let nothing be done through strife or vainglory; but in lowliness of mind let each esteem other better than themselves.","year":64},{"id":"recbNom3HiyNsfJhU","ref":"Phil.2.4","text":"Look not every man on his own things, but every man also on the things of others.","year":64},{"id":"recWnhat0U8NK0qrP","ref":"Phil.2.5","text":"Let this mind be in you, which was also in Christ Jesus:","year":64},{"id":"recjSHyZGWM2GNNjQ","ref":"Phil.2.6","text":"Who, being in the form of God, thought it not robbery to be equal with God:","year":64},{"id":"recTm32xHCSKA4r0U","ref":"Phil.2.7","text":"But made himself of no reputation, and took upon him the form of a servant, and was made in the likeness of men:","year":64},{"id":"recgAeca5JGZWdl2t","ref":"Phil.2.8","text":"And being found in fashion as a man, he humbled himself, and became obedient unto death, even the death of the cross.","year":64}]}
